LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1086
Introduced by Dover, 19.
Read first time January 15, 2026
Committee: Education
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to community college; to amend section
2 85-2005, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska; to change eligibility
3 requirements for community college gap assistance as prescribed; to
4 repeal the original section; and to declare an emergency.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1086 LB1086
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 85-2005, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 85-2005 (1) An applicant for community college gap assistance under
4 the community college gap assistance program shall demonstrate capacity
5 to achieve the following outcomes:
6 (a) The ability to be accepted to and complete an eligible program;
7 (b) The ability to be accepted into and complete a postsecondary
8 certificate, diploma, or degree program for credit;
9 (c) The ability to obtain full-time employment; and
10 (d) The ability to maintain full-time employment over time.
11 (2) The committee may grant community college gap assistance under
12 the community college gap assistance program to an applicant in any
13 amount up to the full amount of eligible costs.
14 (3) Except as otherwise provided in the subsection, the The
15 committee shall deny an application when the community college or other
16 eligible institution receiving the application determines that funding
17 for the total eligible cost as defined in section 85-2006 for an
18 applicant's participation in an eligible program is available from any
19 other public or private funding source. The committee shall not consider
20 any benefit available to an applicant pursuant to the Supplemental
21 Nutrition Assistance Program Employment and Training program administered
22 by the State of Nebraska pursuant to 7 C.F.R. 273.7 as such regulation
23 existed on January 1, 2026, when determining an applicant's eligibility
24 for community college gap assistance.
25 Sec. 2. Original section 85-2005, Reissue Revised Statutes of
26 Nebraska, is repealed.
27 Sec. 3. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
28 passed and approved according to law.
